ZH: 我会在大门口守候你的到来。
EN: I will wait for you at the front gate.

ZH: 她守候着孩子们放学回家。
EN: She waits for the children to come home from school.

ZH: 我守候着我的好朋友出现。
EN: I am waiting for my good friend to show up.

ZH: 他们守候着新年的到来。
EN: They are waiting for the arrival of the New Year.

ZH: 她守候着久违的亲人的归来。
EN: She waits for the long-lost relatives to return.

ZH: 我们守候着太阳升起的那一刻。
EN: We wait for the moment when the sun rises.

ZH: 他一直守候在门口直到深夜。
EN: He waited at the door until late at night.

ZH: 她守候着他的病情有所好转。
EN: She waits for his condition to improve.

ZH: 我守候着她的电话。
EN: I am waiting for her call.

ZH: 我们守候着一场奇迹的发生。
EN: We wait for a miracle to happen.

ZH: 她守候着他的倒下，然后赶紧去帮助他。
EN: She waits for him to fall and then rushes to help him.

ZH: 我们守候着明天的好天气。
EN: We wait for good weather tomorrow.

ZH: 他们守候着会议的结束。
EN: They wait for the meeting to end.

ZH: 我守候着一个机会来救回我的公司。
EN: I wait for an opportunity to save my company.

ZH: 她守候着一切恢复正轨。
EN: She waits for everything to return to normal.

ZH: 我们守候着他们归来。
EN: We wait for their return.

ZH: 他们守候着比赛的结果。
EN: They wait for the result of the game.

ZH: 我守候着这座城市的繁华。
EN: I wait for the prosperity of this city.

ZH: 他守候在门口，准备给客人打开大门。
EN: He waits at the door, ready to open the door for the guests.
